The paper discusses the use of semantic web technologies and ontology-based matching techniques for transforming and linking clinical trials data, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of approximate string matching and evaluation of performance, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the creation of a linked data space, which is related to semantic web technologies (cs.SI).
